TITLE: Pushing Data Chunks to a FileStream
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to add binary data to a FileStream in chunks, which is useful for large files and for tracking upload progress.
SOURCE: https://github.com/garden-co/jazz/blob/main/homepage/homepage/content/docs/using-covalues/filestreams.mdx#2025-04-17_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Create a sample Uint8Array (in real apps, this would be file data)
const data = new Uint8Array([...]);

// For large files, break into chunks (e.g., 100KB each)
const chunkSize = 1024 * 100;
for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i += chunkSize) {
  // Create a slice of the data
  const chunk = data.slice(i, i + chunkSize);

  // Push chunk to the FileStream
  fileStream.push(chunk);

  // Track progress
  const progress = Math.min(100, Math.round((i + chunk.length) * 100 / data.length));
  console.log(`Upload progress: ${progress}%`);
}
```

